            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-14T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-14T03:00:00-05:00" n="1461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.9531/11–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-14T16:00:00+08:00">November 14, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 15—2:55 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1999. Re Contel 1941 [<hi rend="italic">1943</hi>], November 8. Letter November 8
                    to Chou En-lai re Tsingtao property returned by mail today without
                    acknowledgment or comment.</p>
                <p>Tor reference, please inform Peiping any developments favorable or otherwise re
                    matter.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 1999. Department pass Tsingtao.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
